message: The consistent high-score recipe involves cooked vegetables and cooked protein. To get an 80-value item: 1. Combine two raw vegetables, then cook them with the stove (e.g., pepper + potato, then + stove). 2. Cook a raw protein with the stove (e.g., raw beans + stove). 3. Combine the cooked veggie mix with the cooked protein. Alternatively, if you only have one vegetable, cook it with the stove. Then cook two different proteins with the stove. Combine the cooked vegetable with one cooked protein, and then combine that result with the second cooked protein. Grains and water did not increase the value; stick to the cooked veggie-protein combinations. The maximum achievable value with this strategy was 80.
